d police leaders could \"seize power any time\" with slight opposition, but De Gaulle has so far opposed the use of force.\n\nEx-premiers Rene Pleven or Guy Mollet have the best chances of forming a government.\n\nTo limit further political deterioration which would enhance De Gaulle's chances, Coty has called on Socialist leader Guy Mollet to form a government. Mollet's prospects depend heavily on the extent to which Independent deputies balance their favorable personal regard for him against the tough conditions he has posed. In view of the bitterness resulting from the recent debate, it will be difficult for the right to swallow Mollet's insistence on the Algerian statute and the economic program which toppled Bourges-Maunoury and Mollet respectively.\n\nIf Mollet fails, Pleven would probably try essentially the same program in the expectation that a middle-of-the-road deputy would be more readily acceptable to the right. Mollet and Duchet are believed to have agreed in August that in the event of an early crisis over Algeria, which would make cooperation between Socialists and Independents difficult, Pleven would be a good choice to form a \"bridge government\" to reconcile the Socialists and Independents. There is some doubt, however, whether Pleven is as acceptable personally as Mollet to many conservative deputies.\n\nThere is a growing consciousness among the deputies that a grave national crisis must be dealt with speedily", "token_count": 237, "token_end_0based": 236, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "3 french political crisis general de gaulle and a few army and police leaders could seize power any time with slight opposition but de gaulle has so far opposed the use of force ex-premiers rene pleven or guy mollet have the best chances of forming a government to limit further political deterioration which would enhance de gaulle's chances coty has called on socialist leader guy mollet to form a government mollet's prospects depend heavily on the extent to which independent deputies balance their favorable personal regard for him against the tough conditions he has posed in view of the bitterness resulting from the recent debate it will be difficult for the right to swallow mollet's insistence on the algerian statute and the economic program which toppled bourges-maunoury and mollet respectively if mollet fails pleven would probably try essentially the same program in the expectation that a middle-of-the-road deputy would be more readily acceptable to the right mollet and duchet are believed to have agreed in august that in the event of an early crisis over algeria which would make cooperation between socialists and independents difficult pleven would be a good choice to form a bridge government to reconcile the socialists and independents there is some doubt however whether pleven is as acceptable personally as mollet to many conservative deputies there is a growing consciousness among the deputies that a grave national crisis must be dealt with speedily", "unred_source_page": 7}
